<div id="main-article" class="article-content retro-folders">
<p></p><div class="indent"><em>Thy hand, Belinda; darkness shades me / On thy bosom let me rest;</em> <br><em>More I would, but Death invades me / Death is now a welcome guest.</em> <br><em>When I am laid in earth, / May my wrongs create no trouble in thy breast;</em> <br><em>Remember me! but ah! forget my fate.</em><div class="indent">&mdash; <a class="urllink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ePdic5HLb-U">Dido's Lament<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a><em>, from Purcell's</em> Dido and Aeneas, <em>which Dido sings right before committing suicide.</em></div></div><p>There's something about live theatre. Something about being in the same room as the actors, breathing that same air, feeling the vibrations when they fall. Actors are charged when standing before an audience, and stage actors arguably put more into their craft - more time, more stamina, more physical exertion - than your standard TV or film actor.</p><div class="proper-ad-unit mobile-ad square_ad"><h6 class="ad-caption">Advertisement:</h6><div id="proper-ad-tvtropes_mobile_ad_1"><script>propertag.cmd.push(function() { proper_display('tvtropes_mobile_ad_1'); })</script></div></div><p>This pays off.</p><p>With the right cast, with a receptive audience, with beautiful words and maybe the perfect music, death, separation, and injustice on stage can break the heart unlike any other medium. Ready yourself for spoilers.</p><hr>Works with their own pages<p></p><ul><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TearJerker/SeventeenSeventySix" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TearJerker/SeventeenSeventySix">1776</a></em></li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TearJerker/TheTwentyFifthAnnualPutnamCountySpellingBee" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TearJerker/TheTwentyFifthAnnualPutnamCountySpellingBee">The 25th Annual Putnam County Spelling Bee</a></em></li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TearJerker/AidaJohnRice" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TearJerker/AidaJohnRice">Aida (John/Rice)</a></em></li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TearJerker/AidaVerdi" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TearJerker/AidaVerdi">Aida (Verdi)</a></em></li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TearJerker/Anastasia" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TearJerker/Anastasia">Anastasia</a></em></li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TearJerker/Assassins" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TearJerker/Assassins">Assassins</a></em></li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TearJerker/AvenueQ" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TearJerker/AvenueQ">Avenue Q</a></em></li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TearJerker/BeautyAndTheBeast" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TearJerker/BeautyAndTheBeast">Beauty and the Beast</a></em></li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TearJerker/BeMoreChill" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TearJerker/BeMoreChill">Be More Chill</a></em></li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TearJerker/BlackFriday" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TearJerker/BlackFriday">Black Friday</a></em></li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TearJerker/TheBlueBird" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TearJerker/TheBlueBird">The Blue Bird</a></em></li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TearJerker/TheBookOfMormon" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TearJerker/TheBookOfMormon">The Book of Mormon</a></em></li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TearJerker/Cabaret" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TearJerker/Cabaret">Cabaret</a></em></li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TearJerker/Camelot" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TearJerker/Camelot">Camelot</a></em></li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TearJerker/Cats" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TearJerker/Cats">Cats</a></em></li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TearJerker/ChildrenOfEden" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TearJerker/ChildrenOfEden">Children of Eden</a></em></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TearJerker/CirqueDuSoleil" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TearJerker/CirqueDuSoleil">Cirque du Soleil</a><ul><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TearJerker/Alegria" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TearJerker/Alegria">Alegr&iacute;a</a></em></li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TearJerker/MichaelJacksonTheIMMORTALWorldTour" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TearJerker/MichaelJacksonTheIMMORTALWorldTour">Michael Jackson The IMMORTAL World Tour</a></em></li></ul></li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TearJerker/AChorusLine" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TearJerker/AChorusLine">A Chorus Line</a></em></li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TearJerker/ComeFromAway" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TearJerker/ComeFromAway">Come From Away</a></em></li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TearJerker/CyranoDeBergerac" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TearJerker/CyranoDeBergerac">Cyrano de Bergerac</a></em></li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TearJerker/DearEvanHansen" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TearJerker/DearEvanHansen">Dear Evan Hansen</a></em></li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TearJerker/DeathOfASalesman" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TearJerker/DeathOfASalesman">Death of a Salesman</a></em></li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TearJerker/DogSeesGod" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TearJerker/DogSeesGod">Dog Sees God</a></em></li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TearJerker/Dreamgirls" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TearJerker/Dreamgirls">Dreamgirls</a></em></li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TearJerker/Elisabeth" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TearJerker/Elisabeth">Elisabeth</a></em></li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TearJerker/Evita" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.ph